 <h2><U>Instaclick Eye of Zomm</U></h2></center><br><br>Unfortunately, this guide is only of any use to mages. "Wait!" I hear you cry, "Mages already have that spell, right?". Yes, yes we do. But that does NOT make this item worthless. And no, I'm not concerned about the mana this level8 spell uses.<br><br>How much do you use this spell? (Or its older brother: Eye of Tallon). I bet you don't use it much, but it can be very useful. The reason you don't use it, is the effort involved in losing a valuable spell, sitting down and finding eye of zomm, using it, replacing it when done... A lot of effort right? Not to mention sometimes impossible or at least dangerous for the sitting or even spell dropping required. But wait! There is an easier way.<br><br>How about just right clicking an item in your inventory? Sound easier? It takes no mana, no effort, no changing of spells. This means that whenever you want to see whats around the corner, where the tank has got to, if that mob is up... just click. It can be amazingly useful when its an instaclick, a spell you never used before can be rediscovered.<br><br><br>And mages are lucky. There are several items that insta-proc eye of zomm, but we get the only one with unlimited charges!<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/claybracelet.gif"><br><br>Ok. I have hopefully convinced you that this toy is a nice little item to own, now to get you one.<br><br><b><u>Getting the Bracelet</u></b><br><br>OK, you need four quest items named "A Rune of Clay", all identicle, but they all identify differently.<br><br>First stop: The Rathe Mountains. You will be hunting level25 gnomish necros, and can get two at a time with some skeletons, so make sure you can handle it or have help. The gnomes we're looking for are these three:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/gnomes.JPG"><br><br><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3076">Bindlegrob</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3079">Sindlerob</a> and <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3078">Findlegrob</a>, found in the following places in Rathe Mountains:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/rathegnm.jpg"><br><br>Smoke them out and kill them, more than once if you need to, until you have a rune off each. (6 min spawn time if it doesn't drop first try).<br><br>Now your almost there, all you need to do now is find and kill <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=2556">this fella</a> in the Ocean of Tears:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/goblinhm.jpg"><br><br>Look for loc neg1200, neg8560, and you will either find him or a placeholder to kill. He will eventually drop the fourth rune. All you have to do now, is head over to the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/zones/Antonica/Solusek_Ro.htm">Temple of Soulsek Ro</a> and hand them into <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3288">Joyce</a>. Enjoy your new toy!<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br>Zonelookup Failed!